# Camera System

Read `docs/Camera_System_Spec.md` before making any changes.

## Core Design Decisions
- Camera is a `Camera2D` — this is a 2D physics project; do NOT use Camera3D
- Camera is a **sibling of the game world** — NEVER a child of any ship node
- Follow target is any `Node2D`; changing the followed ship = calling `follow(new_target)`
- Uses a **critically damped spring** for position smoothing — do NOT replace with lerp
- Cursor offset shifts the view toward the aim point; scales with zoom level
- No per-frame PerformanceMonitor instrumentation needed (camera costs < 0.01ms)

## Key API
- `follow(target: Node2D)` — set the follow target
- `release()` — clear the follow target (holds current position)
- `get_follow_target() -> Node2D` — query current target

## Watch Out For
- All positions are `Vector2` — this is a 2D camera following 2D nodes
- `zoom` in `Camera2D` is inverse: smaller value = zoomed in (things appear larger)
- The spring velocity (`_velocity: Vector2`) must be reset to `Vector2.ZERO` on `release()`
- `max_cursor_offset` should scale as `max_cursor_offset / zoom.x` to stay consistent at all zoom levels
- Camera must survive player ship destruction — check `is_instance_valid(_follow_target)` each frame
